&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; 2008/9/3 kentb &lt;kentb@...&gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; Jan,
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; You can use JUnit for longer-running tests, but there are some
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; assumptions
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; JUnit embodies that will cause some problems. JUnit assumes tests
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; are
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; atomic--they run or don&#39;t run, they run in unit time. Integration
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; tests
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; often take a long time to run, so interim feedback is valuable.
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; Integration
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; tests can usefully have multiple failures, where that is less
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; common with
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; unit tests. OTOH, tests are tests--independent self-checking bits
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; of code
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; that run and get reported--and for that part of running
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; integration tests
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; JUnit works fine.
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; It seems to me to be a tradeoff between the simplicity of running
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; all tests
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; as JUnit tests and the challenges of getting the integration
&gt; tests
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; to run
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; as
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; JUnit tests. Different contexts will requires different
&gt; solutions.
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; If I had
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; a few integration tests, I&#39;d make them work with JUnit. If I had
&gt; a
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; large
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; suite of integration tests that played a prominent role in
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; development, I
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; would use some other tool and integrate my unit testing results
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; with the
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt; integration results.
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &gt;
